## CopyAttachments

### Overview

This script is designed to copy the attachments from a source workspace and project to a new workspace. The copy is based on matching the _FormattedID_ of the work item from the old workspace to the _OldFormattedID_ in the new workspace.

### Arguments

usage: CopyAttachments

-children                     Include the child projects in the task?

-dw,--destWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;     Destination workspace name to copy to

-h,--help                     Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;               password

-sp,--sourceProject &lt;arg&gt;     Source project to copy attachments from

-sw,--sourceWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;   Source workspace name to copy from

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;               username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;         Rally URL instance

### Example

java â€“jar CopyAttachments.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -sp &quot;Clinical Core Apps Program&quot; -sw &quot;Segment/Clinical TSG&quot; -dw Sample

## CopyProjectStructure

### Overview

This script takes the project identified by the _â€“sp_ argument and the _â€“children_ flag to copy all of the projects in the hierarchy from the source workspace to the destination workspace. This copy includes:

- Project
- Editors
- Team Membership
- Releases
- Iterations
- Iteration Capacities

This script is not able to replicate the Viewer and Admin permissions.

### Arguments

usage: CopyProjectStructure

-children                     Flag to include the child projects

-dw,--destWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;     Destination workspace name to copy to

-h,--help                     Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;               password

-sp,--sourceProject &lt;arg&gt;     Source Project Name

-sw,--sourceWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;   Source workspace name to copy from

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;               username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;         Rally URL instance

### Example

java â€“jar CopyProjectStructure.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -sp &quot;Clinical Core Apps Program&quot; -sw &quot;Segment/Clinical TSG&quot; -dw Sample -children

## FixStoryPermissions

### Overview

After migrating stories and defects, it turns out that some of the Stories and Defects get moved to the Completed state even though they were originally in the Accepted state. This script looks in the source workspace and checks the state of the copied stories and defects to confirm that they are still accepted, if they were originally accepted.

### Arguments

usage: FixStoryPermissions

-children                     Include child projects in the analysis

-dw,--destWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;     Destination workspace name to copy to

-h,--help                     Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;               password

-sp,--sourceProject &lt;arg&gt;     Source Project to check for Accepted work

items

-sw,--sourceWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;   Source workspace name to copy from

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;               username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;         Rally URL instance

### Example

java â€“jar FixStoryPermissions.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -sp &quot;Clinical Core Apps Program&quot; -sw &quot;Segment/Clinical TSG&quot; -dw Sample -children

## MakeProjectReadOnly

### Overview

This script is designed to set all people in a project to a Viewer role. If the _â€“children_ flag is used then all child projects will be set to Viewer. If the Â­_â€“admin_ flag is set then all Project Admins will be switched to viewer. Even after running this script, any Workspace or Subscription Admins will have edit capability within the project.

### Arguments

usage: MakeProjectReadOnly

-admin                        Flag to include project admins

-children                     Flag to include the child projects

-h,--help                     Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;               password

-sp,--sourceProject &lt;arg&gt;     Source Project Name

-sw,--sourceWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;   Source workspace name to copy from

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;               username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;         Rally URL instance

### Example

Java â€“jar MakeProjectReadOnly.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -sp &quot;Clinical Core Apps Program&quot; -sw &quot;Segment/Clinical TSG&quot; -children -admin

## OpennessAndTransparencyMaker

### Overview

In an attempt to provide openness to the work across teams, this script gives everyone enabled in Rally viewer access to the project specified. If the _â€“children_ flag is used, then all of the child projects will also be given Viewer access.

### Arguments

usage: OpennessAndTransparencyMaker

-children               Flag to include the child projects

-h,--help               Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;         password

-pr,--project &lt;arg&gt;     Project Name

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;         username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;   Rally URL instance

-w,--workspace &lt;arg&gt;    Workspace to apply permissions

### Example

Java â€“jar OpennessAndTransparencyMaker.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -pr AIMS -w Sample -children

## UpdateDefaultWorkspace

### Overview

This script looks at the current Default Workspace/Project settings for all users and identifies any that are set to the _sourceWorkspace_ and any of the _sourceProject_ values and then switches it to the _destWorkspace_ and project. The _â€“children_ flag will determine if all child projects should be evaluated or just the _sourceProject_.

### Arguments

usage: UpdateDefaultWorkspace

-children                     Include the child projects in the task?

-dw,--destWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;     Destination workspace name to copy to

-h,--help                     Print this message

-p,--pass &lt;arg&gt;               password

-sp,--sourceProject &lt;arg&gt;     Source Project to look for in the user

profile

-sw,--sourceWorkspace &lt;arg&gt;   Source workspace name to copy from

-u,--user &lt;arg&gt;               username

-url,--rallyUrl &lt;arg&gt;         Rally URL instance

### Example

java â€“jar UpdateDefaultWorkspace.jar -u m35055 -p &lt;password&gt; -url https://rallyonprem.sys.sample.com -sp Hutts -sw &quot;Segment/Clinical TSG&quot; -dw Sample

# Example Usage Flow

When performing a migration, the recommended order of scripts/actions are:

1. _CopyProjectStructure_ java script
2. Export data to excel
3. Massage data
4. Create necessary custom fields
5. Import data from excel into new location
6. Run _FixStoryPermissions_ java script
7. Run _CopyAttachments_ java script
8. Run _OpennessAndTransparencyMaker_ java script to add viewers to project
9. Run _UpdateDefaultWorkspace_ java script
10. Run _MakeProjectReadOnly_ java script to turn the old projects to _read only_
